This paper deals with the problem of maximizing revenue for the seller side in online ads trading platforms. It involves predicting the optimal reserve price for each auction in a dynamical way, which requires techniques from information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). The paper also discusses the use of classifiers to identify high-value inventories, which involves data structures (DS) and statistical inference (SI). Finally, the paper mentions simulations on Yahoo ads exchange (MM), which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (MM) research.
